In case you still haven\xe2\x80\x99t decided how you\xe2\x80\x99re going to make your Turkey, i teamed up with @jennieo to bring you this beautiful and easy Buttermilk Brined Turkey Recipe! :raising_hands::turkey::sparkles:I also wrote out the ultimate Turkey Cooking Guide from everything i learned while doing the #jennieo Turkey Hotline takeover! :nerd_face::thumbs_up: So let\xe2\x80\x99s make the Turkey on my stories now \xe2\x80\x94 you can find the links there and in my profile! :smiling_face_with_3_hearts::two_hearts:

Buttermilk Brined Turkey 
 
1 (12 to 18-pound) @jennieo Fresh Whole Turkey
1 gallon buttermilk
\xc2\xbd cup hot sauce
\xc2\xbd cup salted butter, room temperature
2 tablespoons favorite seasoning, such as a Creole blend
Onion, lemon, orange, garlic, thyme, rosemary and sage, if desired
 
Remove neck and giblets from turkey cavity and set aside. These may be used to prepare gravy or stuffing. The plastic leg clamp should be left on during cooking.
 
In large brining bag or stockpot, combine buttermilk and hot sauce; add turkey, breast side down Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
 
After 24 hours, remove turkey from brine and wipe most of the brine off, leaving a thin coat. Place turkey on rack in shallow pan, breast side up. 
 
Heat oven to 325\xc2\xb0F. Spread butter all over turkey. Sprinkle with seasoning blend.  Fill turkey cavity with onion, lemon, orange, garlic, thyme, rosemary and sage, if desired. Loosely cover turkey with foil. Roast 1 hour. Remove foil. Roast 3\xc2\xbc to 3\xc2\xbe hours or until timer pops up and turkey is fully-cooked, 180\xc2\xb0F as measured by a meat thermometer inserted into the thickest part of the thigh. ALWAYS confirm doneness with a meat thermometer. Juices should run clear. Let turkey stand 20 minutes before carving.'

b"Enjoy S'more @skippybrand peanut butter with Chef @kobe_yn!

Ingredients
4 graham cracker squares
1 Tbsp. SKIPPY:registered: Creamy or SUPER CHUNK:registered: Peanut Butter
2 large marshmallows
2 slices banana

Directions
Evenly spread SKIPPY:registered: Peanut Butter on 2 graham cracker squares. On microwave-safe plate, arrange crackers, then top each with marshmallows. Microwave at HIGH 15 seconds or until marshmallows puff. Top each with banana slice, then remaining graham cracker squares."

b'Meet @hormel.pepperoni\xe2\x80\x99s biggest little fan @kobe_yn! He\xe2\x80\x99s making a Cast Iron Pepperoni Pizza. :pizza::pizza::pizza: Here\xe2\x80\x99s how to whip up this delicious pizza at home:
Ingredients:
1 pound frozen store-bought pizza dough, thawed
1/4 cup olive oil
1/2 cup pizza sauce
4 ounces shredded mozzarella cheese
1/2 cup Hormel:registered: Pepperoni
1/4 cup torn fresh basil
Crushed red pepper and flaked sea salt, as desired
Directions:
Heat to 475\xc2\xb0F. Place a 12-inch cast-iron skillet in the oven to preheat 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, roll or stretch dough into a 14-inch circle. Carefully remove skillet from oven. Drizzle two thirds of the olive oil into skillet, then carefully transfer dough to skillet, pressing dough up edges of pan. Spread pizza sauce over dough. Sprinkle with cheese. Top with pepperoni. Brush dough edges with remaining olive oil. Bake 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.
Transfer to cutting board. Top with torn basil, crushed red pepper and salt, as desired. Cut into slices and serve.'
